The young man, who captured the hearts of many on social with his great voice, has been signed by the popular music executive Jon Jazzy. Ugbekile David Osameke aka Boy Spyce was recently unveiled as the latest Mavin Records signee alongside his debut new EP. Boy Spyce became an internet sensation through several song covers, using his unmistakably unique voice and reflective lyrics. In 2021, his videos became a sensation online as he sang the cover of Davido’s “Jowo”. 		 			Top five Nollywood movies on Netflix in 2022		 		 		 			Wizkid might still owe EME three albums – Banky W		 		 		 			African men don’t abuse women, children – Seun…		 		 He later gave a beautiful performance of Wizkid’s global hit “Essence”. Welcoming Boy Spyce to the Mavin fold, Jon Jazzy shared a video complication of the new artiste with the caption: “Being a tunnel with which a talent is being nurtured is a blessing I would never take for granted. “After being trained in the Mavin academy by the best in the game, world pls help us welcome and follow the newest addition to the @mavinrecords family @boyspyce. MAVIN ACTIVATED.” This latest signee by Mavin Records is coming after the successful introduction of Ayra Starr and Magixx.